Definition: a religion founded by Manes in the third century
Example: a synthesis of Zoroastrian dualism between light and dark and Babylonian folklore and Buddhist ethics and superficial elements of Christianity; spread widely in the Roman Empire but had largely died out by 1000
Synonyms: adj, pert, manichean, manichaean, Manichaeanism, religion, a, founded, by, Manes, in, the, third, century, synthesis, of, Zoroastrian, dualism, between, light, and, dark, Babylonian, folklore, Buddhist, ethics, superficial, elements, Christianity, spread, widely, Roman, Empire, but, had, largely, died, out
Category: noun.cognition
